A code fence whose info string names no language opens no code block; it
folds into the paragraph, where its delimiters read as an inline code
span:

\texttt{python\ \{.foo\}\ code}

Inside such a fold no later line opens a block of its own:

\texttt{not\ a\ language\ \#\ still\ text,\ not\ a\ heading}

A fence with no closing fence folds the same way:

``` unterminated
